Al PICKER, alias Yip, Plaintiff In Error, v. UNITED STATES, Defendant in Error. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. October 15, 1928. No. 88. Leonard A. Snitkin, of New York City (Leo H. Klugherz, of New York City, of counsel), for plaintiff in error. Charles H. Tuttle, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Alvin McKinley Sylvester, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for defendant in error.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and SWAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed.
